ifact beyond the execution metrics file.\n\nPlease inspect `logs/org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-core:1.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-12T12-00-29-944243Z.log`, `logs/org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-core:1.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-12T12-02-27-194382Z.log`, `logs/org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-core:1.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-12T12-03-54-586335Z.log`, `logs/org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-core:1.8/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-12T12-02-27-182956Z.log`, and `stats/org.apache.maven.doxia/doxia-core/1.8/execution-metrics.json`.\n\n1. Recreate `tests/src/org.apache.maven.doxia/doxia-core/1.8` from the existing 1.7 suite, not from the 1.0 API surface; at minimum, update `PipelineSinkTest` to use `org.apache.maven.doxia.sink.impl.PipelineSink` and `org.apache.maven.doxia.sink.impl.SinkAdapter`.\n2. Remove or replace the `SiteModule*` anonymous tests, since `org.apache.maven.doxia.module.site` and `.manager` are not present in `doxia-core:1.8`; if that coverage still matters, move it to the correct module/dependency and target the current API there.\n3. After the javac issues are fixed, rerun `compileTestJava`/`test` for `org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-core:1.8`, then rerun the native lane on a runner with free temp space because the current native retries are blocked by disk exhaustion."}}
